label.value: regulation of replication fork arrest at rDNA repeats

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of replication fork arrest at rDNA repeats.

label.value: protein localization to pericentric heterochromatin

value.value: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in the pericentric heterochromatin.

label.value: regulation of receptor localization to synapse

label.value: negative regulation of receptor localization to synapse

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of receptor localization to synapse.

label.value: positive regulation of receptor localization to synapse

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of receptor localization to synapse.

label.value: mitochondrial outer membrane permeabilization involved in programmed cell death

value.value: The process by which the mitochondrial outer membrane becomes permeable to the passing of proteins and other molecules from the intermembrane space to the cytosol as part of a programmed cell death process.

label.value: glucosidase complex

value.value: A protein complex which is capable of glucosidase activity.

definition.value: An example of this is ygjK in E. coli (P42592) in PMID:23826932.

label.value: regulation of NAD metabolic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of NAD metabolic process.

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of NAD metabolic process.

label.value: positive regulation of NAD metabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of NAD metabolic process.

label.value: respiratory basal cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a respiratory basal cell.

definition.value: Changes in the lineage choice of ABCs or their undifferentiated daughters might contribute to the mucous cell hyperplasia, metaplasia or squamous metaplasia seen in many respiratory disorders

label.value: regulation of neuroblast proliferation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neuroblast proliferation.

label.value: superoxide dismutase complex

value.value: A protein complex which is capable of superoxide dismutase activity.

definition.value: An example of this is SOD1 in Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288c (UniProt symbol P00445) in PMID:10026301.

label.value: superoxide dismutase copper chaperone complex

value.value: A protein complex which is capable of superoxide dismutase copper chaperone activity.

definition.value: An example of this is CCS1 in Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288c (UniProt symbol P40202) in PMID:10426947.

label.value: metallochaperone complex

value.value: A protein complex which is capable of metallochaperone activity.

label.value: glycine catabolic process to isobutanol

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glycine to isobutanol.

label.value: valine catabolic process to isobutanol

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of valine to isobutanol.

label.value: response to plumbagin

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a plumbagin stimulus.

label.value: cellular response to plumbagin

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a plumbagin stimulus.

label.value: GABA receptor complex

value.value: A protein complex which is capable of GABA receptor activity. Upon binding of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA) it transmits the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity. Major inhibitory receptor in vertebrate brain. Also found in other vertebrate tissues, invertebrates and possibly in plants. Effective benzodiazepine receptor.

label.value: GABA-A receptor complex

value.value: A protein complex which is capable of GABA-A receptor activity. In human, it is usually composed of either two alpha, two beta and one gamma chain of the GABA-A receptor subunits or 5 chains of the GABA-A receptor subunits rho1-3 (formally known as GABA-C receptor).

definition.value: An example of this is GBRA1 in human (UniProt symbol P14867) in PMID:18790874.

label.value: G protein-coupled GABA receptor complex

value.value: A protein complex which is capable of G protein-coupled GABA receptor activity. In human, it is usually a heterodimer composed of GABA-B receptor subunits 1 and 2.

definition.value: An example of this is GABR1 in human (UniProt symbol Q9UBS5) in PMID:18790874.

label.value: cell cortex of growing cell tip

value.value: Any cell cortex that is part of a growing cell tip.

label.value: negative regulation of proteoglycan biosynthetic process

label.value: negative regulation of chondrocyte proliferation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of chondrocytes by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. A chondrocyte is a polymorphic cell that forms cartilage.

label.value: positive regulation of chondrocyte proliferation

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of chondrocytes by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. A chondrocyte is a polymorphic cell that forms cartilage.

label.value: regulation of growth plate cartilage chondrocyte differentiation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the process in which a chondroblast acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of a chondrocyte that will contribute to the growth of a bone. A chondrocyte is a polymorphic cell that forms cartilage.

label.value: regulation of receptor-mediated virion attachment to host cell

label.value: positive regulation of receptor-mediated virion attachment to host cell

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of receptor-mediated virion attachment to host cell.

label.value: dendritic filopodium

value.value: A small, membranous protrusion found primarily on dendritic stretches of developing neurons. May receive synaptic input, and can develop into dendritic spines.

definition.value: Dendritic filopodia are generally less-well studied than dendritic spines because their transient nature makes them difficult to detect with traditional microscopy techniques, and because they are sometimes destroyed by sample preparation. Note that filopodia on dendritic shafts are distinct from other types of filopodia (even those found in dendritic growth cones) and may react differently to stimuli, as shown in PMID:12904473.

label.value: regulation of chondrocyte differentiation involved in endochondral bone morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the process in which a chondroblast acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of a chondrocyte that will contribute to the development of a bone. A chondrocyte is a polymorphic cell that forms cartilage.

label.value: apoptotic process involved in development

label.value: regulation of cell cycle G2/M phase transition

value.value: Any signaling pathway that modulates the activity of a cell cycle cyclin-dependent protein kinase to modulate the switch from G2 phase to M phase of the cell cycle.
